<object id="GUID-E0C7A050-2C10-4D89-9DD2-992538FCDF1E" class="- topic/object "><desc class="- topic/desc "><p class="- topic/p ">Set-Reset media step patterns </p></desc><param name="testid" value="156026" class="- topic/param "/><param name="target" value="NIL" class="- topic/param "/><param name="axmodule" value="None" class="- topic/param "/></object> 
</p></section><section id="GUID-92369981-F020-4E62-9707-58F93D054214" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Description</title><p class="- topic/p ">With this test media step patterns can be set and reset. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">These media step patterns will be added during subsequent prints. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If the number of media step patterns is too large, they will overlap in the print, and the measurement will not yield a usable result. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">So check that the media step patterns don't overlap in the print. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Enter a desired number of zero patterns to reset them. 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-69D2CD54-5B44-4236-AE10-A76F8E51C6CC.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>SDS</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
